@Michelleobama, former First Lady of the United States of America, wore a custom #Schiaparelli Haute Couture gown designed by @danielroseberry to the American Portrait Gala last night in Washington D.C. 
Over the course of the evening the museum awarded six honorees with its “Portrait of a Nation Prize”, which celebrates high achievements in the worlds of business, fashion, media, performing arts and science.
Michelle Obama presented the prize in the performing arts category to Lin-Manuel Miranda, the award-winning composer, lyricist, and actor, and creator of Tony Award-winning musicals “In The Heights” and "Hamilton".
